com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.databaseservice

Class SequenceDatabaseSuperService

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.plugin.GeneiousService
      • com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.plugin.GeneiousServiceWithPanel
        • com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.databaseservice.SequenceDatabaseSuperService

  • public abstract class SequenceDatabaseSuperService
extends GeneiousServiceWithPanel
    A plugin should return a service which extends this class if it wishes to provide a Sequence Search facility that can have databases added and removed by the user or if there are some general preferences that apply to the Sequence Datbases of the plugin. This class provides methods for adding and removing databases as well as initial setup and configuration of a group of sequence databases.

    Services that are returned as child services must not extend this class, only services that are returned from GeneiousPlugin.getServices() directly.

    The databases provided by this service must be provided as child DatabaseServices. Each of these must return a non-empty map from DatabaseService.getSequenceSearchPrograms(com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.databaseservice.DatabaseService.SequenceSearchQueryType).

    Sequence database can be provided by a plugin without implementing one of these, the sequence database only need to return a non-empty value from DatabaseService.getSequenceSearchPrograms(com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.databaseservice.DatabaseService.SequenceSearchQueryType).

      • addDatabase

        public void addDatabase(File file,
               String name,
               Options options,
               ProgressListener progressListener,
               DatabaseService.SequenceSearchQueryType expectedDatabaseType)
                 throws DatabaseServiceException
        Add a new sequence database to the service from a file on disk. As a result of this call, a new child service should be added to the service. This method is never called if getDatabaseFileFormatExtensions() returns an empty list. This can happen sometime later as long as the user is aware of progress (eg downloading blast executables).
        Parameters:
        file - a file with one of the extensions specified by getDatabaseFileFormatExtensions() that should be used to populate the database
        name - the name chosen by the user for the database, the new DatabaseService should return this as its name, if a database with this name already exists then the existing database should be replaced.
        options - the options returned from getAddDatabaseOptions(com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.databaseservice.DatabaseService.SequenceSearchQueryType) after they have been displayed to the user
        progressListener - ProgressListener to report progress of the add operation and allow cancelling
        expectedDatabaseType - User selected type for the database, not guaranteed to be correct.
        Throws:
        DatabaseServiceException - if the service failed to add the database for any reason

      • isSetUp

        public boolean isSetUp()
        If this method returns false then the user will not be allowed to choose this service as a search target until they have set it up. If false then getSetupOptions() must return a non-null value so the user can set the service up.

        Default returns true

        Returns:
        whether or not this service has been set up and is ready to process queries

      • getSetupOptions

        public Options getSetupOptions()
        Optionally override to return Options which will be displayed to the user in a services set up section of the interface. If the service must be set up in some way before it can be used then the options returned from this method must allow the user to set up the service. If the service doesn't require set up or if the service has already been set up then these options can be used to further configure the service (eg. The location of the blast executables).

        applySetupOptions(com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.plugin.Options,jebl.util.ProgressListener) is called when these options should be saved.

        If this returns a non-null value then applySetupOptions(com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.plugin.Options,jebl.util.ProgressListener) must also be overriden. Default returns null.

        Returns:
        options for setting up or configuring the service or null for none.

      • applySetupOptions

        public void applySetupOptions(Options setupOptions,
                     ProgressListener progressListener)
                       throws DatabaseServiceException
        Apply and save the specified setup options to the service. This method is called after the options from getSetupOptions() have been displayed to the user and they have clicked OK. If the service is not currently setup (ie isSetUp() returns false) then after this call the service should be setup. This can happen sometime later as long as the user is aware of progress (eg downloading blast executables).
        Parameters:
        setupOptions - Options to apply and save
        progressListener - to report progress of the setup operation and allow cancelling
        Throws:
        DatabaseServiceException - if the setup options couldn't be applied

      • getDatabaseFileFormatExtensions

        public List<String> getDatabaseFileFormatExtensions()
        A list of extensions for file formats that can be added directly to the service. Eg. BLAST supports adding of FastA files. The user will be allowed to choose a file on disk with one of these extensions and it will be added directly to the service without import/export in to Geneious. This allows very large databases to be added.

        If the returned list is empty then the user will be able to select any file. Must not be null

        Default implementation returns an empty list.

        Returns:
        a list of file format extensions which can be added directly to the service or empty list to allow any file to be selectd. Not null

      • supportsAddingDatabasesFromDocumentsOrFiles

        public boolean supportsAddingDatabasesFromDocumentsOrFiles()
        Return true to have the program display options for choosing a file or using the selected documents to create a database. If false then these options will be hidden and only the options from getAddDatabaseOptions(com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.databaseservice.DatabaseService.SequenceSearchQueryType) will be shown.

        Note: if false is returned from this method then addDatabase(com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.documents.AnnotatedPluginDocument[], String, com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.plugin.Options, jebl.util.ProgressListener) will be called with an empty list of documents and when the user clicks OK. If false is returned then the DatabaseService.SequenceSearchQueryType passed in to getAddDatabaseOptions(com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.databaseservice.DatabaseService.SequenceSearchQueryType) should be ignored because options should be returned in all cases.

        Default implementation returns true

        Returns:
        true to show options for choosing a file or documents to populate a database, false to hide the options.

      • getActionsEnabledWhenServiceSelected

        public List<GeneiousAction> getActionsEnabledWhenServiceSelected()
        Description copied from class: GeneiousService
        List of Geneious Actions which can appear in the menu bar, toolbar or popup-menu in the service tree.

        This can be empty (e.g. Collections.emptyList()), but not null. These actions are only enabled when this service is selected. If many services provide actions of the same name from this method then they will be placed under a single menu item/button and the action of that menu item/button is dependent on the selected service. This does not count for popup actions because these are only visible when the service itself is right-clicked (Ctrl+Click on MacOS).

        Overrides:
        getActionsEnabledWhenServiceSelected in class GeneiousService
        Returns:
        list of actions that should be enabled when this service is selected.
